underlying_goal: To set up a new project structure using symlinks and then commit the resulting file changes, specifically a file relocation, to the git repository.
primary_success: Claude demonstrated excellent reasoning by correctly diagnosing a file move instead of a deletion and addition, navigating a symlinked directory structure to find the correct git repository, and executing the entire commit/pull/push workflow flawlessly.
brief_summary: The user initialized a project with a symlinked structure and then asked Claude to commit the work. Claude correctly navigated the symlinks to find the git repo, intelligently identified that a file had been moved rather than deleted and re-added, and then correctly committed, pulled, and pushed the changes.
